# akbarali.dev — Vercel Deployment

## Live setup (verified)

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Vercel project | `akbarali-dev` |
| Team | `akbarali-s-org-vercel` |
| Production URL | https://akbarali-dev.vercel.app |
| GitHub repo | `sodikovakbarali/akbarali-dev` |
| Production branch | `main` |
| Auto-deploy | **Yes** — push to `main` triggers a production deployment |
| Framework | Next.js 15 (App Router), static/content-only (no DB) |
| Node | 24.x |

## What happens on push

1. Commit and push to `main`.
2. Vercel builds automatically (~30–45s).
3. Production alias updates at https://akbarali-dev.vercel.app.

No manual `vercel deploy` is required when Git integration is connected.

## Verify deployment (CLI)

```bash
vercel ls                          # recent deployments + status
vercel inspect akbarali-dev.vercel.app   # current production deployment
vercel whoami                      # confirm logged-in account
```

## Manual deploy (if needed)

```bash
npx vercel deploy --yes            # preview
npx vercel deploy --prod --yes     # production (usually unnecessary)
```

## Agent behavior

- After content changes the user wants live: commit → push to `main` → confirm deploy with `vercel ls` or `vercel inspect`.
- Do **not** assume deploy failed without checking CLI output; auto-deploy is active for this project.
- Prefer Vercel CLI over MCP if the Vercel MCP server is unavailable.
- This site has no secrets in repo; no env vars are required for basic deploys.

